page.title: 10THE OLD FISH DOCK: W. HULL
page.content:
{St.Andrews Dock. }
The dock is on the River Humber, approximately 2 miles from Hull city centre. The dock is not busy at all.There are no ships in sight.There are some lock gates, all silted up, not being used any more.One bit of dock is nearly all mud and no water. There is a strong smell of fish from the nearby fish factories.This fish comes in container lorries from other parts of the country. There are hardly any men working except for some stacking wooden pallets near the side of the dock.
